Xerox Names Ashok Vemuri CEO of Outsourcing Business
Business services division employs more than 100,000 people

 






By

Drew FitzGerald and 
              

Drew FitzGerald
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyDrew FitzGerald
@drewfitzgerald
Google+
andrew.fitzgerald@wsj.com



Anne Steele


Anne Steele
The Wall Street Journal
BiographyAnne Steele
@AnneMarieSteele
anne.steele@wsj.com




  Updated June 14, 2016 9:33 p.m. ET





 Xerox Corp. tapped former iGate Corp. Chief Executive Ashok Vemuri to lead its business services company after the technology giant splits in two later this year. Mr. Vemuri, 48 years old, will become CEO of Xerox Business Services LLC on July 1 and will also be an executive vice president of Xerox until the separation. The business services wing employs more than 100,000 people in areas ranging from for-hire call centers to...
  


